    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e116cf52_594baee8",
        "filename": "go/swarming/autoscaler/autoscaler.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 116,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-31T15:54:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just brain-dumping here:\n\n- bots.cfg will need to specify which bots get the AUTOSCALER_DIMENSION. Therefore, we\u0027ll either need to mark out numeric ranges for specific sets of autoscaled bots, or we\u0027ll need to add another prefix, eg. \"skia-e-medium-123\".\n- For that matter, we probably don\u0027t need an AUTOSCALER_DIMENSION if we add a bot name prefix, although it does make for more efficient queries.\n- We can probably do away with the \"instances\" list altogether, by giving an instance template, name template, and numeric range.\n- Providing the instance type alias as part of the bot ID might allow us to avoid the instance template as well, if we map eg. \"medium\" -\u003e instance_types.LinuxMedium().  When we add dev and internal instances into the mix, this gets a little more complicated.",
      "parentUuid": "00a6c24f_19202b83",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 116,
        "startChar": 52,
        "endLine": 116,
        "endChar": 63
      },
      "revId": "d54a6eeab0ef78354ecff9b6c53213e8def2becc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6523a514_22b65374",
        "filename": "go/swarming/autoscaler/autoscaler.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 116,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-01T15:18:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t have strong opinions about any of this. My vague feeling is that once we have something more-or-less working, we will see what we like and dislike about the setup and then we will have a better idea of what could be improved.\n\nAlmost unrelated idea: I think we may eventually want a general way to be able to associate code that creates/deletes bots (e.g. instance_types.LinuxMedium) with a set of dimensions (e.g. gce:1,machine_type:n1-standard-16,os:Linux); however, I\u0027d like that to be able to work for non-GCE bots, and for subsets of bots, e.g. \"Skolo Win bots\" as well as \"Skolo Win bots with Intel GPU.\" In other words, I slightly dis-prefer using bot name to identify bot group, because then I would need to name win bots like skia-e-win-intel-skylake-NNN, which is a bit verbose (and besides it would be too long for a Windows machine name).",
      "parentUuid": "e116cf52_594baee8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 116,
        "startChar": 52,
