    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3900cd31_8dd00d44",
        "filename": "go/swarming/autoscaler/autoscaler.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 178,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-30T21:23:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If this is the most convenient way to represent dimensions for the future users of this package, then that\u0027s fine, but I\u0027d like to point out that this is different from the (at least) three existing ways to represent bot dimensions: []*swarming.SwarmingRpcsStringListPair, map[string][]string, []string (see\nhttps://skia.googlesource.com/buildbot/+/fe93b540de56ca7fa47262b5b1463ad680676cb5/go/swarming/apiclient.go#482)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 173,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 178,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "d54a6eeab0ef78354ecff9b6c53213e8def2becc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "936f36fa_b3926c3c",
        "filename": "go/swarming/autoscaler/autoscaler.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 178,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-31T15:54:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So the bots normally have the map[string][]string representation, which is analogous to  []*swarming.SwarmingRpcsStringListPair but more convenient.  Tasks have []string, simply because that\u0027s how they\u0027re specified to Swarming.  The map[string]bool is convenient for determining whether a bot can run a task, since we can loop through the task\u0027s dimensions and check the map[string]bool for their presence.\n\nAll of that said, I\u0027m not sure what format we really need right now.  Presumably the Task Scheduler will write a blob of data somewhere indicating the number of task candidates for each dimension set.  We\u0027ll have one autoscaler per type of GCE instance, and each one will match the given candidates up against its own dimensions to determine how many candidates pertain to that scaler.  My best guess at this point is that the task candidate dimensions will be specified using []string and therefore the efficient way of matching them to bot dimensions will be map[string]bool.\n\nFTR, I really don\u0027t like this practice of obtaining the dimensions from the bots on the fly, but it\u0027s probably better than hard-coding them somewhere, or putting them in a config.",
      "parentUuid": "3900cd31_8dd00d44",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 173,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 178,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "d54a6eeab0ef78354ecff9b6c53213e8def2becc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
